From 69aeb9c8ef8e1a5b63639c467dd602b61a3e3089 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramesh Mandal <ramesh@6epixels.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 03:13:34 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(float): replace Document PiP with a dedicated floating
 chat window
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Document Picture-in-Picture is scoped to tabs (one PiP window per tab,
opened from the tab's main browsing context) and is not exposed to
extension side panels — the float could never launch from the panel.

New architecture:
- pip.html entrypoint: standalone compact chat window opened via
  browser.windows.create({type:'popup'}); stays visible when the main
  browser window is minimized; owns its own socket with the same
  identity, announcing presence 'online' (actively chatting); closing
  it drops that socket and the panel's chosen status wins again
- floating-chat.ts: open/close/toggle + window lifecycle tracking
- server: roster deduped per username with presence priority
  (online > busy > away > offline) — required now that one user can
  hold multiple sockets (panel + float), also fixes the latent
  duplicate-roster bug for any multi-window user
- appendMessage dedupes by message id (both windows receive server
  events; history is shared via persisted storage)
- ChatView float button toggles the window; dead Document-PiP code
  removed; Settings copy corrected (floating window, not always-on-top)
